          <ul class="card-text">
            <li>The Sun is all the colors mixed together this appears white to our eyes.</li>
            <li>The Sun is composed of hydrogen 70% and Helium 28%.</li>
            <li>The Sun is 109 times wider than the Earth and 330,000 times as massive.</li>
            <li>One million Earths could fit inside the Sun.</li>
            <li>The distance between the Earth and the Sun is an Astronomical Unit</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://solarsystem.nasa.gov/solar-system/sun/overview/" target="_blank"
